The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

Life

 A Bollywood blast

 Glimpses from the Bollywood theme party at Ankur Apartments. Pictures by Sanjoy Chattopadhyaya 

 Gabbar Singh plays the perfect host, Mangal Pandey takes charge backstage, Bunty and Babli play pranks on the guests ? an all-action Bollywood bash of, by and for residents of Ankur apartments on Lord Sinha Road, on Sunday night.

 A Goodlife glimpse?

 Name of complex: Ankur Apartments

 Address: 10 Lord Sinha Road

 No of flats: 64

 Theme: Bollywood, Bollywood and more Bollywood.

 Stage: The lawns and the compound, done up with posters of movies. The performance area resembled a movie theatre.

 Team: Each and every member of the building chipped in. More than 50 slipped into Bollywood garb.

 Show: Fusion song, dance and filmi sequences from Black to Mughal-e-Azam, Dilwale Dulhaniya Le Jayenge to Don.

 Sip--bite: After films, food. An Italian, Mexican and Chinese spread was on offer.

 Voiceover: The post Diwali meet is the most awaited programme in the complex. The elders are as excited as the youngsters, says Raj Somani, secretary, Ankur. The party has a theme every year; this year we paid tribute to the spirit and contribution of Bollywood.




